<section id=3D"qr-with-pivoting">
<h3>QR with Pivoting<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://labs.acme.byu.e=
du/Volume1/QR_Decomposition/QR_Decomposition.html#qr-with-pivoting" title=
=3D"Link to this heading">#</a></h3>
<p>The LU decomposition can be improved by employing Gaussian elimination w=
ith partial pivoting, where the rows of <span class=3D"math notranslate noh=
ighlight"><mjx-container class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML=
" tabindex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=3D"317" style=3D"font-size: 103.9%; posit=
ion: relative;"><mjx-math class=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-mi cl=
ass=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D434 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-math=
><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable=3D"on" display=3D"inline"><math xmlns=3D"h=
ttp://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>A</mi></math></mjx-assistive-mml></m=
jx-container></span> are strategically permuted at each iteration.
The QR factorization can be similarly improved by permuting the columns of =
<span class=3D"math notranslate nohighlight"><mjx-container class=3D"MathJa=
x CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=3D"318=
" style=3D"font-size: 103.9%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class=3D"MJX-T=
EX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D434=
 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable=3D"on" =
display=3D"inline"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>A=
</mi></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> at each iteration.
The result is the factorization <span class=3D"math notranslate nohighlight=
"><mjx-container class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabind=
ex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=3D"319" style=3D"font-size: 103.9%; position: rel=
ative;"><mjx-math class=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-mi class=3D"m=
jx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D434 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mi class=3D"m=
jx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D443 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mo class=3D"m=
jx-n" space=3D"4"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c3D"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-mi class=
=3D"mjx-i" space=3D"4"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D444 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><=
mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><=
/mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable=3D"on" display=3D"inline"><math x=
mlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>A</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>=3D</mo=
><mi>Q</mi><mi>R</mi></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span>, wh=
ere <span class=3D"math notranslate nohighlight"><mjx-container class=3D"Ma=
thJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=3D=
"320" style=3D"font-size: 103.9%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class=3D"M=
JX-TEX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1=
D443 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable=3D"=
on" display=3D"inline"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><=
mi>P</mi></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> is a permutatio=
n matrix that encodes the column swaps.
To compute the pivoted QR decomposition with <code class=3D"docutils litera=
l notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">scipy.linalg.qr()</span></code>, set the=
 keyword <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">p=
ivoting</span></code> to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span=
 class=3D"pre">True</span></code>.</p>
<div class=3D"highlight-pycon3 notranslate"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre i=
d=3D"codecell7" tabindex=3D"-1"><span></span><span class=3D"go"># Get the d=
ecomposition AP =3D QR for a random matrix A.</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">A</span> <span cla=
ss=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n">np</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><s=
pan class=3D"n">random</span><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">ra=
ndom</span><span class=3D"p">((</span><span class=3D"mi">8</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"mi">10</span><span class=3D"p">))</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">Q</span><span clas=
s=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">R</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span=
 class=3D"n">P</span> <span class=3D"o">=3D</span> <span class=3D"n">la</sp=
an><span class=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">qr</span><span class=3D"p">(=
</span><span class=3D"n">A</span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"=
n">pivoting</span><span class=3D"o">=3D</span><span class=3D"kc">True</span=
><span class=3D"p">)</span>

<span class=3D"go"># P is returned as a 1-D array that encodes column order=
ing,</span>
<span class=3D"go"># so A can be reconstructed with fancy indexing.</span>
<span class=3D"gp">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=3D"n">np</span><span cla=
ss=3D"o">.</span><span class=3D"n">allclose</span><span class=3D"p">(</span=
><span class=3D"n">Q</span> <span class=3D"o">@</span> <span class=3D"n">R<=
/span><span class=3D"p">,</span> <span class=3D"n">A</span><span class=3D"p=
">[:,</span> <span class=3D"n">P</span><span class=3D"p">])</span>
<span class=3D"go">True</span>
</pre><button class=3D"copybtn o-tooltip--left" data-tooltip=3D"Copy" data-=
clipboard-target=3D"#codecell7">
      <svg xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class=3D"icon icon-tabler i=
con-tabler-copy" width=3D"44" height=3D"44" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" stroke-wi=
dth=3D"1.5" stroke=3D"#000000" fill=3D"none" stroke-linecap=3D"round" strok=
e-linejoin=3D"round">
  <title>Copy to clipboard</title>
  <path stroke=3D"none" d=3D"M0 0h24v24H0z" fill=3D"none"></path>
  <rect x=3D"8" y=3D"8" width=3D"12" height=3D"12" rx=3D"2"></rect>
  <path d=3D"M16 8v-2a2 2 0 0 0 -2 -2h-8a2 2 0 0 0 -2 2v8a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h2">=
</path>
</svg>
    </button></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id=3D"qr-via-givens">
<h3>QR via Givens<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D"https://labs.acme.byu.edu/=
Volume1/QR_Decomposition/QR_Decomposition.html#qr-via-givens" title=3D"Link=
 to this heading">#</a></h3>
<p>The Householder algorithm uses reflections to triangularize <span class=
=3D"math notranslate nohighlight"><mjx-container class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_=
Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=3D"321" style=3D"=
font-size: 103.9%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-hi=
dden=3D"true"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D434 TEX-I"></m=
jx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectable=3D"on" display=3D"=
inline"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>A</mi></math=
></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span>.
However, <span class=3D"math notranslate nohighlight"><mjx-container class=
=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_coun=
ter=3D"322" style=3D"font-size: 103.9%; position: relative;"><mjx-math clas=
s=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"=
mjx-c1D434 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectab=
le=3D"on" display=3D"inline"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Mat=
hML"><mi>A</mi></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> can also =
be made upper triangular using rotations.
To illustrate the idea, recall that the matrix for a counterclockwise rotat=
ion of <span class=3D"math notranslate nohighlight"><mjx-container class=3D=
"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=
=3D"323" style=3D"font-size: 103.9%; position: relative;"><mjx-math class=
=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"m=
jx-c1D703 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-mml unselectabl=
e=3D"on" display=3D"inline"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Math=
ML"><mi>=CE=B8</mi></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> radia=
ns is given by</p>
<div class=3D"math notranslate nohighlight">
<mjx-container class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" display=
=3D"true" tabindex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=3D"324" style=3D"font-size: 103.9=
%; position: relative;"><mjx-math display=3D"true" class=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-h=
idden=3D"true" style=3D"margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px;"><mjx-mtable s=
tyle=3D"min-width: 9.623em;"><mjx-table><mjx-itable><mjx-mtr><mjx-mtd style=
=3D"text-align: right;"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"m=
jx-c1D445 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style=3D"vertical-align: -0.1=
5em;"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i" size=3D"s"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D703 TEX-I">=
</mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-script></mjx-msub><mjx-mo class=3D"mjx-n" space=3D"4=
"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c3D"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-mrow space=3D"4"><mjx-mo c=
lass=3D"mjx-s3"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c5B TEX-S3"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-mtabl=
e justify=3D"right" style=3D"min-width: 5.782em;"><mjx-table><mjx-itable><m=
jx-mtr><mjx-mtd style=3D"padding-right: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0.2em;"><mjx=
-mi class=3D"mjx-n"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c63"></mjx-c><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c6=
F"></mjx-c><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c73"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-mo class=3D"mjx-n=
"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c2061"></mjx-c></mjx-mo><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i" space=
=3D"2"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D703 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-tstrut></mjx=
