le=3D"on" display=3D"inline"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Mat=
hML"><mi>A</mi></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span> is symmet=
ric, its upper Hessenberg form is a <em>tridiagonal</em> matrix, meaning it=
s only nonzero entries are on the main diagonal, the first subdiagonal, and=
 the first superdiagonal.
This is because the <span class=3D"math notranslate nohighlight"><mjx-conta=
iner class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" ctx=
tmenu_counter=3D"396" style=3D"font-size: 103.9%; position: relative;"><mjx=
-math class=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-msub><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx=
-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D444 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style=3D=
"vertical-align: -0.15em;"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i" size=3D"s"><mjx-c class=
=3D"mjx-c1D458 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-script></mjx-msub></mjx-math><=
mjx-assistive-mml unselectable=3D"on" display=3D"inline"><math xmlns=3D"htt=
p://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mi>k</mi></msub></math></=
mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-container></span>=E2=80=99s zero out everything bel=
ow the first subdiagonal of <span class=3D"math notranslate nohighlight"><m=
jx-container class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=
=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=3D"397" style=3D"font-size: 103.9%; position: relat=
ive;"><mjx-math class=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx=
-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D434 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-math><mjx-assi=
stive-mml unselectable=3D"on" display=3D"inline"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.=
w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>A</mi></math></mjx-assistive-mml></mjx-contain=
er></span> and the <span class=3D"math notranslate nohighlight"><mjx-contai=
ner class=3D"MathJax CtxtMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" ctxt=
menu_counter=3D"398" style=3D"font-size: 103.9%; position: relative;"><mjx-=
math class=3D"MJX-TEX" aria-hidden=3D"true"><mjx-msubsup><mjx-mi class=3D"m=
jx-i"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D444 TEX-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi><mjx-script style=
=3D"vertical-align: -0.308em; margin-left: 0px;"><mjx-texatom size=3D"s" te=
xclass=3D"ORD"><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-ss"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D5B3 TEX-SS">=
</mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-texatom><mjx-spacer style=3D"margin-top: 0.18em;"></=
mjx-spacer><mjx-mi class=3D"mjx-i" size=3D"s"><mjx-c class=3D"mjx-c1D458 TE=
X-I"></mjx-c></mjx-mi></mjx-script></mjx-msubsup></mjx-math><mjx-assistive-=
mml unselectable=3D"on" display=3D"inline"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org=
/1998/Math/MathML"><msubsup><mi>Q</mi><mi>k</mi><mrow data-mjx-texclass=3D"=
ORD"><mi mathvariant=3D"sans-serif">T</mi></mrow></msubsup></math></mjx-ass=
istive-mml></mjx-container></span>=E2=80=98s zero out everything to the rig=
ht of the first superdiagonal.
Tridiagonal matrices make computations fast, so computing the Hessenberg fo=
rm of a symmetric matrix is very useful.</p>
